{"title_page": "Tarun Chandra", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2015}}\n{{BLP sources|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| bgcolour      = \n| name          = Taarun Chandrra\n| image         =https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=i&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=imgres&cd=&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0ahUKEwj9z_vemszKAhWJWhoKHZRuCXYQjRwICTAA&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.galatta.com%2Fkannada%2Fphotos%2Flargeimage%2Factor%2Ftarun-chandra%2F16850%2F&psig=AFQjCNF3N_I2_jZmuFfIjV2KgXOnhAQzZQ&ust=1454060267414205 \n| imagesize     = \n| caption       = \n| birthname     = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1983|4|27}}\n| birth_place    = [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]], [[India]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| othername     = \n| yearsactive   = 2003-present\n| homepage      = \n| occupation    = [[Actor]]\n}}\n\n'''Tarun Chandra''' ({{lang-kn|\u0ca4\u0cb0\u0cc1\u0ca3\u0ccd \u0c9a\u0c82\u0ca6\u0ccd\u0cb0}}; born 27 April 1983), [[Mononymous person|mononymously]] credited as '''Tarun''', is an [[India]]n film actor based in [[Kannada cinema|Kannada Film Industry]]. He made his film debut in the multi-starrer ''[[Khushi (2003 Kannada film)|Khushi]]'' (2003) and has since then acted in various films, notably being, ''Geleya'' (2007), ''[[Love Guru (Kannada film)|Love Guru]]'' (2008) and ''[[Gaana Bajaana]]'' (2010).\n\n== Early life ==\nTarun was born in Bangalore. He graduated his B.Com degree in MES College, Bangalore. He underwent three months acting course at Kishore Namit Kapoor Acting Institute, before he entered into films. He first appeared as one of the lead actors in 2003 released film, ''[[Khushi (2003 Kannada film)|Khushi]]''. After Geleya, Hani Hani's successful run, he was approached for Parichaya and by director Prashant for his movie ''[[Love Guru]]'', which won a state award for best movie.<ref>http://entertainment.oneindia.in/kannada/news/2010/tarun-chandra-interview-gaana-bajaana-271010.html</ref> He had also acted in a Telugu film Valliddari Vayasu Padahare which was released in 2006.\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year !! Film !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Khushi (2003 Kannada film)|Khushi]]'' ||  ||                  \n|-\n| 2006 || ''Valliddari Vayasu Padahare'' || Vamsee || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Geleya]]'' || Vishwa ||  \n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Ee Bandhana]]'' ||  ||\n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[Hani Hani (film)|Hani Hani]]'' || Rahul ||                \n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[Love Guru (Kannada film)|Love Guru]]'' || Pratham ||\n|-\n| 2009 ||''Parichaya'' || Jayanth  ||          \n|-\n| 2009 || ''Seena'' || Seena ||  \n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Gaana Bajaana]]'' || Krish || \n|- \n| 2011 || ''Naanalla'' || Siddharth ||\n|- \n| 2011 || ''Achu Mechu'' || Vijay ||\n|-\n| 2012|| ''[[Addhuri]]'' || Tarun  || Guest appearance\n|-   \n| 2012 || ''[[Ondu Kshanadalli]]'' || Shyam || \n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Snehitaru]]'' ||  || \n|-\n| 2013 || ''Pade Pade'' || Sunny || \n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[Gharshane]]'' || Himself || Special appearance\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Goa (2015 film)|Goa]]'' || || \n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|3749070/}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chandra, Tarun}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Kannada cinema]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Bangalore]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2015}}\n{{BLP sources|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| bgcolour      = \n| name          = Tarun Chandra\n| image         =https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=i&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=imgres&cd=&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0ahUKEwj9z_vemszKAhWJWhoKHZRuCXYQjRwICTAA&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.galatta.com%2Fkannada%2Fphotos%2Flargeimage%2Factor%2Ftarun-chandra%2F16850%2F&psig=AFQjCNF3N_I2_jZmuFfIjV2KgXOnhAQzZQ&ust=1454060267414205 \n| imagesize     = \n| caption       = \n| birthname     = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1983|4|27}}\n| birth_place    = [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]], [[India]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| othername     = \n| yearsactive   = 2003-present\n| homepage      = \n| occupation    = [[Actor]]\n}}\n\n'''Tarun Chandra''' ({{lang-kn|\u0ca4\u0cb0\u0cc1\u0ca3\u0ccd \u0c9a\u0c82\u0ca6\u0ccd\u0cb0}}; born 27 April 1983), [[Mononymous person|mononymously]] credited as '''Tarun''', is an [[India]]n film actor based in [[Kannada cinema|Kannada Film Industry]]. He made his film debut in the multi-starrer ''[[Khushi (2003 Kannada film)|Khushi]]'' (2003) and has since then acted in various films, notably being, ''Geleya'' (2007), ''[[Love Guru (Kannada film)|Love Guru]]'' (2008) and ''[[Gaana Bajaana]]'' (2010).\n\n== Early life ==\nTarun was born in Bangalore. He graduated his B.Com degree in MES College, Bangalore. He underwent three months acting course at Kishore Namit Kapoor Acting Institute, before he entered into films. He first appeared as one of the lead actors in 2003 released film, ''[[Khushi (2003 Kannada film)|Khushi]]''. After Geleya, Hani Hani's successful run, he was approached for Parichaya and by director Prashant for his movie ''[[Love Guru]]'', which won a state award for best movie.<ref>http://entertainment.oneindia.in/kannada/news/2010/tarun-chandra-interview-gaana-bajaana-271010.html</ref> He had also acted in a Telugu film Valliddari Vayasu Padahare which was released in 2006.\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year !! Film !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Khushi (2003 Kannada film)|Khushi]]'' ||  ||                  \n|-\n| 2006 || ''Valliddari Vayasu Padahare'' || Vamsee || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Geleya]]'' || Vishwa ||  \n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Ee Bandhana]]'' ||  ||\n|-\n| 2008 